reviewText: Confusing and Frustrating. I do not recommend this course unless you are already an Accountant.   The Course itself is flawed withing the quizzes and possibly poor editing of the videos makes passing quizzes on the first go around very difficult.  I took 2 Bookkeeping Courses prior to this course and I feel that is the ONLY reason I was able to complete this course.  This may be a Continuing Education Course for Accountants NOT a course for beginners!Good Luck! I recommend Intuit's  Academy of Bookkeeping

A very good course on Accounting over 8 weeks, at a pace that is just right. It covers each of the financial statements that are required, as well as other important topics like ratios, revenue recognition and the time value of money. The highlight of the course is the final submission, where we have to bring together everything we learned, and analyze the 10K Report of a public company of our choosing. You learn a lot in this course, and I am very glad to have taken it.
